Anna Karenina;;1997;;PG-13;;Drama,Romance;;6.3;;Bernard Rose;;Sophie Marceau,Sean Bean,Alfred Molina,Mia Kirshner,James Fox,Fiona Shaw,Danny Huston,Phyllida Law,David Schofield,Saskia Wickham,Jennifer Hall,Anna Calder-Marshall,Valerie Braddell,Pyotr Shelokhonov,Niall Buggy,Anthony Calf,Vernon Dobtcheff,Hamish Falconer;;Anna is a young and elegant wife of Mr. Karenin, who is wealthy and old. She meets the handsome Count Vronsky. Anna and Vronsky fall in love with each other, and he comes to be with her in St. Petersburg. They are very happy together and make a great looking couple, but soon their happiness gets under social pressures. Anna is hopelessly begging Mr. Karenin for a divorce, but he wants to keep the mother of their child. She has another baby born from her lover Vronsky. Conflict between her untamed desires and painful reality causes her a depression and suicidal thoughts.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0118623/